This paper deals with Simultaneous Localization and Mapping (SLAM) algorithms, which are commonly used in robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses Monte Carlo simulation results, which suggests that it may fall under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The proofs and analysis of the algorithm's properties suggest that it may also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with the convergence and consistency properties of the algorithm, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
